			<div class="commentcount">466</div>

				<p>I have always done the same thing (just did it 10 minutes ago) but my little trick is to make a full batch, and just prior to adding the raisins I divide the dough and make half raisin and the other half chocolate chip.</p>
<p>Then I bake up one cookie sheet of each and scoop the remaining dough onto a wax paper covered cookie sheet.  I put the &#8220;extra&#8221; into the freezer until they are frozen then I put them into a vacuum bag.  Saves me time next time I need a fix.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
